teraturhistorischen Erforschung der Emotionen und schärft den Blick für die Medialität von Gefühlskulturen im geschichtlichen Wandel. Die Diskussion methodologischer Fragen bietet interdisziplinäre Anschlussmöglichkeiten.  aHistorical research into emotionality is at present generally enjoying an heightened level of interest. This bilingual volume documents the proceedings of an international conference, discussing current paradigms and perspectives in historical literary research into emotions and heightening awareness of the mediality of cultures of emotion in historical change. The discussion of methodological questions opens up avenues for interdisciplinary research.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aEmotions in literaturevCongresses. 0aLiterature, MedievalxHistory and criticismvCongresses. 4aAffekt /i.d.Literatur. 4aHistorische Anthropologie. 4aMittelalter /Literatur. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh1 aANDERSSON, THEODORE M ., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEMING, JUTTA, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGRUBMÜLLER, KLAUS, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHAUBRICHS, WOLFGANG, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHAUFE, HENDRIKJE, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHUBER, CHRISTOPH, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJAEGER, C. STEPHEN, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJaeger, C. Stephen, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKASTEN, INGRID, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKELLER, HILDEGARD ELISABETH, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1